git -r done

11 December 2015

git

I’m trying to get a handle on git and using it with GitHub lately. I use GitHub to house most of my main projects I’m working on. This site is hosted on GitHub Pages. I actually haven’t edited any code on this site yet. It’s been an expirement with Jekyll and GitHub pages. I forked a Jekyll site on GitHub and edit through the browser with prose.io. So far this site has never touched my computer locally.

Anyways git has been a little harder to remeber commands and use. I found a very nice looking site that reads easy at Attlasion. For a more indepth look I found git dudes have pretty extensive guides to using git.
